"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167397","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-08","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government continues to attach high priority to the reduction of unnecessary EU bureaucracy. We have called on the European Commission to step up its efforts in this area, and we therefore welcome the fact that the Commission has created the new post of First Vice-President (Frans Timmermans) with specific responsibility for Better Regulation across the entire Commission.</p><p> </p><p>We succeeded in securing agreement on very positive Conclusions at the 4 December EU Competitiveness Council, which call on the EU institutions to enhance efforts to reduce the overall regulatory burden, and call on the Commission to develop and put in place reduction targets in particularly burdensome areas, especially for SMEs.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, as I reported in my Written Ministerial Statement of 6 November (Column 51WS), since October 2013, 10 out of the 30 recommendations of the Business Taskforce report, “Cut EU red tape”, have been achieved, saving businesses over £200 million, as highlighted in the Taskforce’s progress report published last month at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/cut-eu-red-tape-business-taskforce-report-one-year-on" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/cut-eu-red-tape-business-taskforce-report-one-year-on</a></p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-12-08T15:42:06.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167397/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167397/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167397/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167397/answer/previousversion/31971","Biography information for Matt Hancock","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-12-02","Bureaucracy: EU Action","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent steps he has taken at a EU level to reduce bureaucracy.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","216821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167398","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-08","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Following the introduction of the EU services directive, the UK has been a leader in pushing for consistent implementation across member states. More recently, the UK published a non-paper on further services liberalisation which has been widely shared in Europe. Its recommendations have attracted considerable support. We have seen positive signals on services liberalisation from the new Single Market Commissioner, Elżbieta Bieńkowska, in her keynote speech on 18<sup>th</sup> November and services liberalisation also features in the Commission’s recently published ‘Investment Plan for Europe’.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-12-08T15:41:15.14Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167398/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167398/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167398/answer/previousversion/31968","Biography information for Matt Hancock","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-12-02","Service Industries: EU Action","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what progress he has made on services liberalisation at an EU level; and if he will make statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","216820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167399","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-05","<p>The Government has received many representations on this significant judgment about holiday pay. My Rt Hon Friend the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills has convened a Taskforce of business representatives and Government departments to assess how we can limit the negative impact on business and jobs.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We are also discussing the implications of the judgment with a wide range of other representative bodies.</p><p> </p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-12-05T14:13:36.233Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167399/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167399/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167399/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-12-02","Holiday Leave: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what representations the Government has received on the decision of the Employment Appeal Tribunal of 4 November 2014 in Bear Scotland and others v Mr David Fulton and others.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","216899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167400","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-05","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government respects the Employment Appeal Tribunal judgment on holiday pay and is urgently working through the detail.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Employers and workers can contact the ACAS helpline on 0300 123 1100 for free and confidential advice if they have any queries on their rights and responsibilities in respect of holiday pay.</p><p> </p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-12-05T14:16:23.19Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167400/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167400/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167400/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-12-02","Holiday Leave: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what response the Government plans to make to the Employment Appeal Tribunal decision of 4 November 2014 in Bear Scotland and others v Mr David Fulton and others.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","216900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167401","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-08","<p>Relations with stakeholders in the supply sectors are operational matters for the office of the Groceries Code Adjudicator, which is an independent statutory regulator established by the Groceries Code Adjudicator Act 2013.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The GCA’s first Annual Report for the period ending 31<sup>st</sup> March 2014 confirms that the Adjudicator had by that date participated in events attended by over 3,000 suppliers and their representative bodies – including those from the dairy, arable and livestock sectors.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Annual Report may be viewed at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/322415/10143-GCA-Annual_Report_2014.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/322415/10143-GCA-Annual_Report_2014.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p><em> </em></p><p> </p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson","216921 ; 216924","2014-12-08T14:49:34.663Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167401/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167401/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167401/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-12-02","Groceries Code Adjudicator","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, on how many occasions the Groceries Code Adjudicator has met stakeholders engaged in production and processing within the (a) beef and (b) grain industry.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mr Mike Weir","216918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167402","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-08","<p>The Groceries Code Adjudicator is an independent regulator established under the Groceries Code Adjudicator Act 2013. Decisions relating to the exercise of the Adjudicator’s statutory powers of investigation are therefore matters for the Adjudicator.</p><p> </p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson","216922 ; 216925","2014-12-08T14:55:04.313Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167402/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167402/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-12-02","Groceries Code Adjudicator","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether the Groceries Code Adjudicator has undertaken research pursuant to the launch of an investigation into issues connected with the (a) beef and (b) grain industry.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mr Mike Weir","216919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167403","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-08","<p>The Groceries Code Adjudicator is an independent regulator established under the Groceries Code Adjudicator Act 2013 to oversee and enforce the Groceries Supply Code of Practice.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Adjudicator has a statutory duty to arbitrate disputes under the Code referred to it by direct suppliers; and has the power to conduct an investigation where it has reasonable grounds to suspect that the Code has been breached.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In each case, such decisions relating to the exercise of the Adjudicator’s statutory powers are matters for the Adjudicator. The Adjudicator has published its prioritisation principles in guidance on its investigation and enforcement functions.<em> </em>The guidance may be viewed at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/325842/GCA_Statutory_Guidance_post_consultation_final_June_14.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/325842/GCA_Statutory_Guidance_post_consultation_final_June_14.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson","216923 ; 216926 ; 216928","2014-12-08T14:51:53.463Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167403/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167403/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167403/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-12-02","Groceries Code Adjudicator","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if the Groceries Code Adjudicator will make it his policy to prioritise work relating to the (a) beef and (b) grain industry.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mr Mike Weir","216920"
