"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167437","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-12-05","<p>An assessment of mobile telephone coverage of the whole of the UK, including Wrexham and West Cheshire and Chester, has been carried out by Ofcom and is publicly available on the Regulator’s web site: <a href="http://maps.ofcom.org.uk/mobile-services/" target="_blank">http://maps.ofcom.org.uk/mobile-services/</a> The information provided goes down to the level of an appropriate administrative area – such as Wrexham. It is not possible to identify data separately for Wrexham town centre</p><p>This covers both 2G and 3G networks and may be consulted on the basis of geographical area or premises. Coverage in each area is ranked from 1 to 5 on the level of mobile coverage (1= 95% or more; 2= 90% - less than 95%; 3= 80% - less than 90%; 4= 60% - less than 80%; 5= less than 60%). It is also possible to download the data in tabular form. The data was last up-dated on 13 December 2013. More information may be found in Ofcom’s 2013 up-date to its Infrastructure Report, also available to download at: <a href="http://maps.ofcom.org.uk/mobile-services/" target="_blank">http://maps.ofcom.org.uk/mobile-services/</a></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","216828 ; 216829","2014-12-05T09:54:32.42Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167437/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167437/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-12-02","Mobile Broadband: Wrexham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of mobile telephone coverage in Wrexham County Borough.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","216830"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167438","Women and Equalities","false","2014-12-09","<p>We are currently considering the form and timing of the public consultation in the light of ongoing caste discrimination litigation in the Employment Appeal Tribunal. We will await the outcome of the judgment before deciding in what form to issue the public consultation</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2014-12-09T19:54:31.76Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167438/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167438/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2014-12-02","Castes: Discrimination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, on what date she plans to issue the public consultation as outlined in the Government's timetable for implementing caste discrimination legislation of 29 July 2013.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","216917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167439","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-09","<p>Outside of the Launch and Recovery phase only UK personnel operated UK Reaper aircraft in Afghanistan.</p><p>UK and US personnel operated both nation's Reaper aircraft as part of the Launch and Recovery phase. Information on the number of occasions that USAF personnel did so is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-12-09T17:26:29.447Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167439/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167439/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-02","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on how many occasions the United States Air Force has used a Royal Air Force Reaper Remotely Piloted Air System in Afghanistan in each year; how many times it released weapons; and what weapons were released.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","216916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167440","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-05","<p>The NATO MQ-9 Users Group will promote cooperation, commonality, cost efficiency, and interoperability between members but will not generate operational capability. The first meetings are due to be held in Paris during January 2015.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-12-05T13:39:46.707Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167440/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167440/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-02","NATO Response Force","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the written Answer of 17 November 2014 to Question 213740, whether the NATO MQ9 Users Group will be available for use as part of the NATO rapid reaction force.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","216827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167441","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-09","<p>Consistent with industry best practice for all projects, Pegasus is under regular review to ensure it meets the Ministry Of Defence's requirements effectively. There are no specific closing dates for these activities.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-12-09T17:23:24.067Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167441/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167441/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-02","AWE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when the closing date will be for the review into the costs and construction timetable of Project Pegasus.","false","Biography information for Alison Seabeck","Plymouth, Moor View","Alison Seabeck","216803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167442","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-05","<p>I am withholding this information as its disclosure would or would be likely to prejudice operational capability, effectiveness or security; also relations between the United Kingdom and other states.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-12-05T13:38:39.877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167442/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167442/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-02","Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether any personnel from Reaper Squadron 39 have been deployed to (a) Al Udeid air base, Qatar, (b) Al Minhad airbase, United Arab Emirates and (c) Al Musannah airbase, Oman.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","216796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167443","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-05","<p>Laser designators on UK Reapers have not been used to mark targets in Syria.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-12-05T13:39:11.48Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167443/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167443/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-02","Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Written Statement of 21 October 2014, Official Report, column 63WS, whether laser designators on UK Reapers carrying out surveillance missions in Syria are marking targets.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","216785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167444","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-05","<p>There have been a series of recent checks to confirm the adequacy of the IT systems used in the national security vetting process. These include: a comprehensive Defence Information Assurance audit, penetration tests and the re-awarding of the vetting system by the Defence Assurance Information Secretary. In addition, a complete refresh of all the electronic forms used in the vetting process is planned to take place in 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-12-05T13:37:04.423Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167444/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167444/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-02","Vetting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent assessment he has made of the adequacy of IT systems used in the national security vetting process.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","216756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167445","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-01-06","<p>Ministers have received a small number of letters from hon. Members about delays in the national security vetting process.</p><p> </p><p>Processing requests for National Security Vetting clearances are, by nature, very robust as they help to establish the integrity of the applicant. Defence Business Services National Security Vetting (DBS NSV) is also reliant upon a number of third party suppliers to complete the security checks.</p><p> </p><p>This has been exacerbated by a key third party supplier encountering difficulties with their IT system, which is outside of the control of the Ministry of Defence. However, these issues have now been resolved and additional personnel have been recruited to address the high volumes of applications.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-01-06T17:11:49.78Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167445/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167445/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167445/answer/previousversion/31992","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-02","Vetting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent representations he has received about delays in the national security vetting process.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","216757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167446","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-09","<p>Women in the Armed Forces already serve on the front line, having taken on an increasingly broad range of roles since the early 1990s.</p><p>As the hon. Member will be aware, a review into the possibility of women serving in ground close combat roles is in progress.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-12-09T17:27:31.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167446/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167446/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167446/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-02","Armed Forces: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that women soldiers are trained for front-line service.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","216753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167447","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-09","<p>As part of its continuing energy efficiency programme the Ministry of Defence has invested in 1,400 energy efficiency projects. These include insulation measures as well as Building Energy Management Systems, boiler controls and LED lighting. These have been delivered across 223 Defence sites both in the UK and overseas.</p><p>Energy efficiency improvements are undertaken as part of all Service Family Accommodation (SFA) upgrade programmes where appropriate. SFA improvements include new or improved loft insulation, external wall insulation and new doors, windows, boilers and heating systems.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-12-09T17:22:18.517Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167447/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167447/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-02","Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he has taken to insulate his departmental estate in order to improve energy efficiency; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","216837"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167448","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-08","Further to my answer of 15 October 2014 to Question 209575, the UK has withdrawn all of its remotely piloted air systems from Afghanistan and has no plans to return them.","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-12-08T16:35:56.533Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167448/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167448/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167448/answer/previousversion/31986","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-02","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 15 October 2014 to Question 209575, whether the Government has had any discussions with the administration of the US on future basing of UK Reapers in Afghanistan in connection with Operation Resolute Support 2015.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","216885"
