"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167533","Home Office","false","2014-12-08","<p>On 29 March 2007 in a Written Ministerial Statement the Prime Minister announced a Machinery of Government Change whereby the transfer of a number of policy areas would take place from the Home Office to a new Ministry of Justice. This included the transfer of the National Offender Management Service, including the Prison and Probation Services, on 9th May 2007. Incorporated in this change was the policy relating to the secure estate for young offenders.<br><br>Section 46 of the Children and Young Persons act 1969 contains provision for the cessation of approved schools as a consequence of the establishment of community homes. The responsibility for approved schools was transferred to the Department of Health and Social Security in 1971 and, in 1973, under a number of orders made under powers in section 46 above approved schools ceased to operate in 1973.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-12-08T16:51:02.857Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167533/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167533/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167533/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-12-02","Young Offender Institutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when responsibility for secure institutions for children, including approved schools, transferred away from the Home Office to other Government departments; and to which other departments and bodies that responsibility was transferred.","false","Biography information for John Hemming","Birmingham, Yardley","John Hemming","216864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167534","Home Office","false","2014-12-18","<p /> <p>The Home Office has used social media as one of many channels and approaches to deliver crime prevention and public awareness communications campaigns. <br><br>The attached table outlines the campaigns for which advertisements have been placed on social media, and a breakdown of how much was spent on this channel per campaign by the Department over the past five financial years. <br><br>The same points to note apply, specifically:<br>• Spend includes net media costs, excluding production and related fees, and VAT.<br>• Costs for 2014/15 shows campaign spend to date. <br>• There was no spend in the 2010-11 Financial Year due to a Government-wide freeze on marketing and advertising spend.<br>Costs regarding ‘other activity related to social media’ include the cost to measure online conversation (‘buzz monitoring’) on social media channels as a way to evaluate campaign effectiveness.</p><p /> <p /> <p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-12-18T18:01:13.867Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167534/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167534/answer","PQ 216938 TABLE.docx","PQ 216938 TABLE.docx","Spending on Campaigns","Spending on Campaigns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167534/answer","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167534/answer/previousversion/31895","Biography information for Karen Bradley","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-12-02","Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 1 December 2014 to Question 215990, for which campaigns advertisements have been placed on social media; and how much was spent in that fashion on each such campaign.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","216938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167535","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-05","<p>The UK’s investment into the CP3 Asia Fund, named ‘Asia Climate Partners’, is a Cayman Islands based Limited Partnership. The UK’s investment into the IFC Catalyst Fund is through a Scottish limited partnership. The tax jurisdiction is therefore in the Cayman Islands for Asia Climate Partners, and in Scotland for the Catalyst Fund. There are no fees charged by either limited partnership. These jurisdictions were chosen because they comply with the OECD Global Forum on Transparency and Exchange of Information for Tax Purposes.</p><p> </p><p>The IFC Catalyst Fund reached first close in November 2012 and the Asia Climate Partners reached first close in November 2014.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne","216944 ; 216946","2014-12-05T14:08:15.163Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167535/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167535/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167535/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","International Climate Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, with reference to the intervention statement for the Climate Public Private Partnership (CP3) Platform, which private equity firm manages the Scottish Limited Partnership for the UK's investment in the CP3 Asia Fund through this Scottish Limited Partnership; and what the cost is of the fees charged by the Scottish Limited Partnership.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","216945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167536","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-05","<p>The UK’s investment into the CP3 Asia Fund, named ‘Asia Climate Partners’, is a Cayman Islands based Limited Partnership. The UK’s investment into the IFC Catalyst Fund is through a Scottish limited partnership. The tax jurisdiction is therefore in the Cayman Islands for Asia Climate Partners, and in Scotland for the Catalyst Fund. There are no fees charged by either limited partnership. These jurisdictions were chosen because they comply with the OECD Global Forum on Transparency and Exchange of Information for Tax Purposes.</p><p> </p><p>The IFC Catalyst Fund reached first close in November 2012 and the Asia Climate Partners reached first close in November 2014.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne","216944 ; 216945","2014-12-05T14:08:15.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167536/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167536/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167536/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","International Climate Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the tax jurisdiction is for the Climate Public Private Partnership (CP3) Asia Fund and (b) International Finance Corporation Catalyst Fund.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","216946"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167537","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-05","<p>The Legal Assistance for Economic Reform (LASER) programme began its implementation phase on 1 June 2014 and is working to improve the investment climates in eight countries across sub Saharan African and Asia, superseding its target to be engaged in six countries by 30 November 2014. DFID has allocated £4.7m to the LASER programme over three and half years.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-12-05T14:24:04.43Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167537/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167537/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167537/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Developing Countries: Administration of Justice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what progress she has made in scaling up her Department's commercial legal programme LASER; and what funding has been allocated to LASER.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Gavin Shuker","216936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167538","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-05","<p>The UK’s investment into the CP3 Asia Fund, named ‘Asia Climate Partners’, is a Cayman Islands based Limited Partnership. The UK’s investment into the IFC Catalyst Fund is through a Scottish limited partnership. The tax jurisdiction is therefore in the Cayman Islands for Asia Climate Partners, and in Scotland for the Catalyst Fund. There are no fees charged by either limited partnership. These jurisdictions were chosen because they comply with the OECD Global Forum on Transparency and Exchange of Information for Tax Purposes.</p><p> </p><p>The IFC Catalyst Fund reached first close in November 2012 and the Asia Climate Partners reached first close in November 2014.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne","216945 ; 216946","2014-12-05T14:08:15.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167538/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167538/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167538/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","International Climate Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, with reference to intervention statement for the Climate Public Private Partnership (CP3) Platform, for what reason the UK's investment in the CP3 Asia Fund is made via a Scottish Limited Partnership.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","216944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167539","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-05","<p>The intergovernmental negotiations process will commence in 2015 and the final framework of goals and targets is subject to negotiation in this forum.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-12-05T14:23:01.91Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167539/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167539/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167539/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Developing Countries: Sustainable Development","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, which stand-alone goals and targets the Government hopes to achieve in the forthcoming inter-governmental negotiations on the sustainable development goals.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Gavin Shuker","216934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167540","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-05","<p>The Open Working Group Report’s proposals show that significant progress has been made in building consensus around the importance of including peace, jobs and justice in the final post-2015 framework.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-12-05T14:23:27.527Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167540/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167540/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167540/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Developing Countries: Sustainable Development","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what progress the Government has made in negotiating specific targets for the delivery of peace, jobs and justice in the sustainable development goals.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Gavin Shuker","216935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167541","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-05","<p>The DFID Direct Roadshows have incurred no costs to the department.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2014-12-05T14:07:42.617Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167541/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167541/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167541/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Charities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much her Department has spent on its DfID Direct roadshows.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Gavin Shuker","216932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167542","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-05","<p>According to the most recent progress reports, 121 women have received mentoring and/or advice through the package announced at the G8 Deauville Partnership conference.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-12-05T14:22:14.64Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167542/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167542/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167542/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Arab States","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many women in business in the Arab world have received mentoring and expert advice from counterparts in the UK and other G8 countries as part of the package announced at the G8 Deauville Partnership conference in London in June 2013.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Gavin Shuker","216933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167543","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-05","<p>A rapid, point-of-care diagnostic test for the Ebola virus will be trialled in the coming weeks at the Ebola treatment centre in Conakry, Guinea. The trial is one of six health research projects that have been jointly funded by the Wellcome Trust and the UK government. If a point-of-care diagnostic test is shown to be ready for use in the response, it will be rolled out as quickly as possible across the region.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-12-05T14:21:22.4Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167543/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167543/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167543/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to encourage the wider roll-out across Africa of recently trialled tests for Ebola used in Guinea.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","216898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167544","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-05","<p>The UK remains a strong and active supporter of Gavi, the Vaccine Alliance. The UK recently pledged up to £1 billion to Gavi for 2016 to 2020. The full UK contribution to Gavi will save a child’s life every two minutes. This funding will be disbursed in tranches on an annual basis. The full UK funding will be released so long as the total amount committed by donors meets Gavi’s replenishment target of $7.5 billion. Whether this threshold has been met will be assessed by DFID officials continually over the period 2016 – 2020.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2014-12-05T14:07:09.023Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167544/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167544/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167544/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Global Alliance for Vaccines and Immunisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, at what intervals her Department plans to fund Gavi, the Vaccine Alliance between 2016 and 2020; what threshold will have to be met by other donors to ensure that her Department's funding to that organisation can be released; and at what intervals her Department plans to assess whether that threshold has been met.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","216797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167545","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-09","<p>As was made clear at the London Conference on Afghanistan, it is vital that women and girls are put at the heart of political, economic and social life in Afghanistan for the country to develop successfully. Gender equality is mainstreamed across all DFID programming, so our entire annual budget of c£10bn for 2014-15 will contribute towards this.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In Afghanistan, DFID programmes to support women and girls include both direct measures, such as training for female Provincial Councillor candidates; and indirect, including our support for education sector salaries. The latter has contributed towards over 2.5 million girls attending school according to the latest figures from the Afghan Ministry of Education.</p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-12-09T15:35:54.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167545/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167545/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167545/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what projects her Department has which involve working with women in Afghanistan; and what the 2014-15 budget is for each such project.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","216770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167546","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-09","<p>My Department regularly consults with women’s rights organisations and women in developing programming to tackle violence against women and girls (VAWG). Over the last few months, this has included several roundtables with representatives from diaspora communities in the UK and women’s rights organisations from across the world on FGM and other forms of VAWG, as well as meetings with representatives from the Gender and Development network and other women’s rights organisations.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2014-12-09T15:36:31.567Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167546/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167546/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167546/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-02","Developing Countries: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department has taken to consult women's rights organisations and women in developing programming for its strategic priority on tackling violence against women.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","216771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167547","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-12-05","<p /> <p>Information on the number of offenders in prison by self-declared religion (including Islam) in England and Wales is published routinely in the ‘Offender Management Statistics Quarterly bulletin’ and can be found in Table 1.5. Copies of the publication are available from the Library of the House and via the following link:</p><p><a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368442/prison-population-q3-2014.xls" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368442/prison-population-q3-2014.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368442/prison-population-q3-2014.xls</a></p><p>Please note that the religion of prisoners is self declared and prisoners are under no obligation to declare their religion.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2014-12-05T14:53:50.747Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167547/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167547/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167547/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-12-02","Prisoners: Islam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many Muslim prisoners there are in England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","216881"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167548","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-12-08","<p>Operational responsibility for coroner services lies with local authorities and any assessment of the timeliness of toxicological analysis by LGC Forensics is a matter for them. The Ministry of Justice has responsibility only for coroner law and policy. It has not made, and would not make such an assessment.</p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"2014-12-08T15:05:49.573Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167548/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167548/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167548/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-12-02","Coroners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what recent assessment he has made of the timeliness of the provision of toxicological analysis by LGC Forensics to coroners in England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","216866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167549","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-12-08","<p>The Legal Aid Agency did not hold a contract with a firm called Mackeys for the period in question and therefore no payments were made and there are no payments outstanding.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-12-08T15:59:35.877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167549/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167549/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167549/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-12-02","Legal Aid Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much the firm Mackeys received in legal aid in (a) 2012-13 and (b) 2013-14; how much in legal aid to this firm is currently outstanding for 2014-15; and to whom such money will now be paid.","false","Biography information for Austin Mitchell","Great Grimsby","Austin Mitchell","216862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167550","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-12-15","<p>The Terrorism Prevention and Investigations Act 2011 came into force in December 2011, and the first TPIM notices were imposed in January 2012. No TPIM notices were in force prior to January 2012.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total Expenditure (£'000)</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>519</p></td><td><p>363</p></td><td><p>221</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The table above shows the total legal aid expenditure on Control Order/TPIM proceedings for each of the last 3 financial years. In the transitional period of 2011-2012 control orders and TPIM were not differentiated for legal aid billing purposes, and this data is not comparable.</p><p> </p><p>This represents between 0.03 – 0.05% of civil and total Legal Aid cash spend for the four years in question.</p><p> </p><p>Anyone facing a trial, or issue where their liberty may be at risk, is eligible to apply for legal aid to ensure they have access to justice. The Legal Aid Agency rigorously assesses all applications on the basis of financial means and merits.</p><p>The Ministry of Justice does not hold any spend data on <em>legal advice and representation</em> associated to cases on the TPIMs regime as the administration costs of legal aid for applicants entitled to legal aid under paragraph 45 Schedule 1 LASPO 2012, which is where TPIMs sit, would not be classed as legal advice and representation.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-12-15T13:50:30.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167550/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167550/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167550/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-12-02","Terrorism Prevention and Investigation Measures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much was spent on legal aid for Terrorism Prevention and Investigation Measures (TPIMs) suspects in each of the last four years; and how much his Department spent on legal advice and representation associated to cases on the TPIMs regime in each such year.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","216939"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167551","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-12-08","<p>The Government takes this issue seriously though measures to deal with it are primarily for the Northern Ireland Executive.</p><p>I am aware that one of the aims of the Northern Ireland Executive’s United Community strategy is to meet the needs of young people, including those from a Protestant working class background.</p><p>Through the Economic Pact agreed in June 2013, this Government provided additional borrowing powers to support projects which promote a shared society, including schools and further education colleges, which will contribute towards meeting the needs of young people from a range of backgrounds including the group referred to in the hon Member’s question.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-12-08T13:02:30.92Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167551/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167551/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167551/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-12-02","Community Development: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what assistance her Department is giving to tackle feelings of isolation among working class Protestant youth.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","216768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167552","Scotland Office","false","2014-12-05","<p>The members of the HMRC's Scotland Act Implementation Programme Board are:</p><p>Sarah Walker (HMRC, Senior Business Sponsor)</p><p>Geoff Yapp (HMRC, Senior Business Sponsor Stamp Duty Land Tax)</p><p>Angela Walker (HMRC, Senior Business Sponsor Scottish Rate of Income Tax)</p><p>David Swift (HMRC, Deputy Director - Strategic Finance Budget Controller)</p><p>Sean Neill (Scottish Government)</p><p>HMT, (Fiscal Devolution)</p><p>Scotland Office, (Economic Adviser)</p><p>HMRC, (Internal Audit)</p><p>HMRC, (Programme Manager)</p><p>HMRC, (Landfill Tax Policy)</p><p>HMRC, (Chief Digital Information Office).</p><p>Freedom of Information principles have been applied and names of staff below SCS grade are not released.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael",,"2014-12-05T15:56:21.813Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167552/answer","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167552/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167552/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-12-02","Income Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, pursuant to the Answer of 11 November 2014 to Question 213288, what the name and job title is of each member of the programme board.","false","Biography information for Margaret Curran","Glasgow East","Margaret Curran","216948"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167553","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2014-12-09","<p>The number of Electoral Registration Officers (EROs) who did not meet one or more of the Commission’s performance standards in each year since their introduction in 2008 is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>299</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>185</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>60</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>67</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>32</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>23</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>In 2013 the Commission introduced a new performance standards framework for EROs to support them in preparing for and delivering the transition to Individual Electoral Registration. In March 2014 we reported that no EROs failed to meet the first of these standards.</p><p>More detailed information on the performance of EROs in each year is available on the Commission’s website.</p><p>The Commission has not to date made any recommendations to the Secretary of State to issue a direction to individual EROs.</p><p>Where an ERO does not carry out their duties in full, the Commission’s priority is to take action to ensure that the ERO makes improvements to their performance in the discharge of their functions. In doing this, the Commission considers the full range of available options, taking into account the facts in each particular case. This could include making a recommendation to the Secretary of State to issue a direction to the ERO to require them to make improvements.</p>","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter",,"2014-12-09T13:17:30.883Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167553/answer","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167553/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167553/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2014-12-02","Electoral Registration Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for South West Devon, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, on how many occasions Electoral Registration Officers did not meet the Electoral Commission performance standards; how many directions were issued by the Commission in response to such occasions; and on how many such directions Ministers have acted.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","216888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167554","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-05","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA) received Mrs Slater’s letter of appeal on 19 November and responded on 3 December 2014.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-12-05T10:23:46.903Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167554/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167554/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167554/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency plans to respond to the letter of appeal from Mrs T. Slater of Christchurch of 14 November 2014.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","216882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167555","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-05","<p>The following Coastguards are employed at the National Maritime Operations Centre in Fareham:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Role </strong></td><td><strong>Grade </strong></td><td><strong>No. </strong></td></tr><tr><td>National Maritime Operations Commanders</td><td>Grade 7</td><td>5</td></tr><tr><td>Maritime Operations Controllers</td><td>Senior Executive Officer</td><td>5</td></tr><tr><td>Maritime Operations Specialists</td><td>Higher Executive Officer</td><td>6</td></tr><tr><td>Senior Maritime Operations Officers</td><td>Executive Officer</td><td>12</td></tr><tr><td>Maritime Operations Officers</td><td>Administrative Officer</td><td>33</td></tr><tr><td>Coastguard Trainer</td><td>Higher Executive Officer</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td>Coastguard Trainer</td><td>Senior Executive Officer</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Total </strong></td><td><strong>66</strong></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The inflow of staff between (i) January to June 2014 was 33 and (ii) July to November was 33.</p><p> </p><p>The outflow of staff between (i) January to June 2014 was 0 and (ii) July to November was 0.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-12-05T13:16:50.12Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167555/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167555/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167555/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","HM Coastguard: Fareham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many Coastguard officials, of what grades are employed at the National Maritime Operation Centre in Fareham; and what the (a) inflow and (b) outflow of such staff was before (i) January and June 2014 and (ii) July and November 2014.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","216896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167556","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-05","<p>For the period October to November 2014 there were no occasions when the night shift at the National Maritime Operations Centre in Fareham was staffed below four people.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-12-05T10:24:30.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167556/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167556/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167556/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","HM Coastguard: Fareham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 1 December 2014 to Question 216240, on how many occasions the number of staff working the night shift at the National Maritime Operation Centre in Fareham in the period October to November 2014 was three or fewer.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","216895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167557","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-09","<p>I have no specific estimate of the average cost incurred or earnings lost by road users whose vehicles are incapacitated following sideswipe collisions attributable to heavy goods vehicles.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Transport’s published accident values for use in project and policy appraisal comprise several costs elements, including the lost output (or earnings) of those injured in road accidents. The values are averages across all reported accidents and are provided by accident severity and road class.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-12-09T11:30:00.603Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167557/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167557/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167557/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","Large Goods Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the average cost incurred or earnings lost by road users whose vehicles are incapacitated following sideswipe collisions attributable to heavy goods vehicles.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mr Mike Weir","216848"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167558","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-09","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The number of heavy goods vehicles (HGVs) involved in accidents that resulted in a personal injury and were reported to the police in the last five years with a) a stationary vehicle and (b) a non-stationary vehicle where the heavy goods vehicle was changing lane to the left or right can be found in the tables below:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>a) </strong><strong>Number of HGVs involved in reported personal-injury accidents with a stationary vehicle where the HGV was changing lane to the left or right: GB, 2009-2013</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Changing lane to left</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Changing lane to right</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>8</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>7</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>5</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong>b) </strong><strong>Number of HGVs involved in reported personal-injury accidents with a non-stationary vehicle where the HGV was changing lane to the left or right: GB, 2009-2013</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Changing lane to left</p></td><td><p>302</p></td><td><p>332</p></td><td><p>284</p></td><td><p>248</p></td><td><p>252</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Changing lane to right</p></td><td><p>417</p></td><td><p>400</p></td><td><p>348</p></td><td><p>331</p></td><td><p>325</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>719</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>732</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>632</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>579</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>577</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The non-stationary vehicle may have been undertaking a number of different manoeuvres such as reversing, performing a U-turn, slowing/stopping or moving off. The HGV manoeuvre in all the above figures was changing lane to the left or right.</p><p> </p><p>These figures come from police reported accident data. They only include accidents in which at least one person was injured and were reported to the police.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-12-09T13:01:54.13Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167558/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167558/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167558/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","Large Goods Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of trends in the number of incidents in which heavy goods vehicles have sideswiped vehicles which are (a) stationary and (b) in transit at the time of collision over the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mr Mike Weir","216847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167559","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-09","<p>The annual report on the longer semi-trailer (LST) trial published in June 2014 included an interim assessment of collisions involving vehicles participating in the trial. This is published on the Government’s website and can be found at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-of-the-longer-semi-trailer-trial-annual-report-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-of-the-longer-semi-trailer-trial-annual-report-2013</a></p><p> </p><p>This report includes analysis of reported road collisions involving LSTs resulting in injury, which shows that the incidence of such collisions is lower than that for the GB Articulated fleet in general. Longer semi-trailer trial vehicles operating between September 2012 and December 2013 were involved in five incidents in which someone was injured, 4 of them slight injuries and one serious injury (broken arm). Of these, one slight and one serious injury occurred on public roads, the remainder in depots or other private areas.</p><p> </p><p>For the general population of heavy goods vehicles, casualty data are only available for incidents that occur on public roads. Comparing these data, longer semi-trailer trial vehicles were involved in injury incidents on public roads at a rate of 48.8 per billion vehicle kilometres. This compares with a rate of 187.4 injury incidents per billion vehicle kilometres for all articulated heavy goods vehicles in Great Britain over the period 2010-2012. The number of casualties in incidents involving all articulated HGVs was an average of over 3,400 per year over this period.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the report estimated that between 600 thousand and 900 thousand HGV vehicle kilometres have been removed from the road as a result of longer semi-trailer operations between September 2012 and December 2013. This will help to further reduce the risk of incidents occurring.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-12-09T11:42:01.25Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167559/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167559/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167559/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","Large Goods Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what interim assessment he has made of the incidence of collisions involving vehicles participating in the Longer HGV Semi-Trailer Trial.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mr Mike Weir","216850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167560","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-09","<p>Guidance in the book <em>The Official DVSA Guide to Driving Goods Vehicles</em> is revised in response to feedback and research. The last time the advice on lane discipline was revised was in a reprint in June 2011 where two paragraphs were added. There have been no changes since.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-12-09T11:33:28.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167560/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167560/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167560/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","Large Goods Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the guidance in respect of (a) lane discipline and (b) related testing requirements for heavy goods vehicles was last revised.","false","Biography information for Mike Weir","Angus","Mr Mike Weir","216849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167561","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-09","<p>Negotiations about changes to EU Directive 96/53/EC are continuing under the Italian Presidency.　 We support proposed changes to the directive to allow extra length to enable new cab designs, with the timings to be determined in Type Approval legislation. We support the completion of the negotiations as soon as possible.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-12-09T11:26:42.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167561/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167561/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167561/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","Large Goods Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent representations he made to his EU counterparts on delays in the introduction of the revised EU Directive 96/53 on vehicle cab design.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","216798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167562","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-09","<p>In the June 2013 spending round, 15 smart motorway interventions were confirmed for delivery post 2015. The M27 J4 – J11 was one of 15 locations identified.</p><p> </p><p>The Highways Agency has been progressing traffic modelling, technical/environmental surveys, development of the operational concept and design work. This will support delivery of a programme of smart motorway solutions across the 15 locations.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-12-09T11:24:44.513Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167562/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167562/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167562/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","M27","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress has been made on making the stretch of motorway between junctions 4 and 11 of the M27 a smart motorway.","false","Biography information for Mr Mark Hoban","Fareham","Mr Mark Hoban","216802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167563","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-05","<p>The Government has a longstanding policy of funding estuarial crossings through tolls. Work on a new Lower Thames Crossing has assumed that it will be tolled, although no decisions have yet been made. Beyond this, there are no plans for further tolls. The £15 billion to be invested in strategic roads over the next five years, set out most recently in the Road Investment Strategy, is wholly funded by Government.</p><p> </p><p>The new Mersey Gateway Bridge and existing Silver Jubilee Bridge will be tolled when the new bridge opens in 2017, although these are the responsibility of Halton Council.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-12-05T10:28:53Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167563/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167563/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167563/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","Tolls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to introduce further toll roads.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","216819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167565","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-05","<p>The following Coastguards are employed at the Coastguard Operations Centre in Falmouth:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Role </strong></td><td><strong>Grade </strong></td><td><strong>No. </strong></td></tr><tr><td>Maritime Operations Controllers</td><td>Senior Executive Officer</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>Maritime Operations Specialists</td><td>Higher Executive Officer</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>Senior Maritime Operations Officers</td><td>Executive Officer</td><td>9</td></tr><tr><td>Maritime Operations Officers</td><td>Administrative Officer</td><td>3</td></tr><tr><td>Watch Manager</td><td>Executive Officer</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>Watch Officer</td><td>Administrative Officer</td><td>7</td></tr><tr><td>Coastguard Watch Assistant</td><td>Administrative Assistant</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Total </strong></td><td><strong>24 </strong></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The inflow of staff between (i) January to June 2014 was 0 and (ii) July to November was 3.</p><p> </p><p>The outflow of staff between (i) January to June 2014 was 2 and (ii) July to November was 1.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-12-05T13:25:06.263Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167565/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167565/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167565/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","HM Coastguard: Falmouth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many coastguard officials of which grades are employed at Falmouth Maritime Rescue Coordination Centre; and what the (a) inflow and (b) outflow was of staff members between (i) January and June 2014 and (ii) July and November 2014.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","216940"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167566","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-05","<p>The new HM Coastguard national network currently consists of the National Maritime Operations Centre and the Coastguard Operations Centre (CGOC) in Falmouth. They can provide cover for each other in the event of either site not being available.</p><p> </p><p>The level of resilience will increase as more centres transition into the national network. The Coastguard Operations Centre in Holyhead comes on line on 15 December 2014.</p><p> </p><p>The programme will complete in December 2015 when the following centres will have joined the national network, at the date specified:</p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Milford Haven – February 2015</li></ul></p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Humber – April 2015</li></ul></p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Aberdeen – July 2015</li></ul></p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Shetland – August 2015</li></ul></p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Belfast – September 2015</li></ul></p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Stornoway – October 2015</li></ul></p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Dover – December 2015</li></ul></p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-12-05T10:27:44.92Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167566/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167566/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167566/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","HM Coastguard: Fareham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many Maritime Rescue Coordination Centre stations are available to act as emergency cover in the event of an emergency at the Maritime Operations Centre in Fareham.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","216942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167567","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-05","<p>On the night watch of 1 December there were three staff at Falmouth, comprising two Senior Maritime Operations Officers and one Watch Officer.</p><p> </p><p>The Maritime Operations Controller was also called into the night watch as contingency for any hand over of operations from the National Maritime Operations Centre (NMOC). This was due to a gas leak in a road near to the NMOC. However no handover was required.</p><p> </p><p>This process was handled in accordance with rehearsed business continuity plans and is an example of the excellent level of resilience within the new HM Coastguard network.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2014-12-05T10:26:41.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167567/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167567/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167567/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","HM Coastguard: Falmouth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many officers of what rank were on watch during the night shift at Falmouth Maritime Rescue Coordination Centre on the night of 1 December 2014.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","216941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167568","Women and Equalities","false","2014-12-05","<p>Due to a technical error, the answer to question 205841 was not processed, as had been believed. I apologise and can confirm to the Rt. Hon. Member that the question has now been answered.</p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-12-05T09:51:08.997Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167568/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167568/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167568/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2014-12-02","Government Equalities Office: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, when she plans to Answer Question 205841, tabled on 15 July 2014.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","216887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167569","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-05","<p>The department has made a number of improvements to reduce times. For example, we have significantly increased staffing resources and improved IT processes. The improvements also include both providers increasing the number of health professionals they employ and opening more assessment centres.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-12-05T10:24:23.707Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167569/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167569/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167569/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-02","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent steps he has taken to reduce the length of time it takes for a decision to be reached on eligibility for personal independence payments.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","216884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167570","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-05","<p /> <p>Following Matthew Oakley’s report we have implemented a number of improvements to communications to ensure that claimants understand the sanctions process and can take the necessary action.</p><p>An investigation of housing benefit with local authorities showed that the IT solution is working to specification and correct notifications are being sent. As a safeguard we have also improved guidance to ensure that staff advise all claimants, when sanctioned, to inform their local authority so that their housing benefit is not inadvertently stopped.</p><p>We will continue to monitor the position in cooperation with local authorities.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-12-05T15:02:34.52Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167570/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167570/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167570/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-02","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the Government's commitment in its response to the Oakley Review, Cm 8904, to implement an IT solution so that local authorities are given the information they need to suspend housing benefit only in cases where it is appropriate to do so, what progress has been made in implementing such a solution; whether the planned implementation date of Autumn 2014 was achieved; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","216814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167571","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-05","<p /> <p>The information as requested is not available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-12-05T13:31:28.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167571/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167571/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167571/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-02","Jobseeker's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many families claiming jobseeker's allowance with dependent children have been sanctioned since October 2012; and how many such people have subsequently had their sanction rescinded.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","216812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167572","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-05","<p /> <p>The information as requested is not available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-12-05T10:38:40.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167572/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167572/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167572/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-02","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many families claiming employment and support allowance with dependent children have been sanctioned since December 2012; and how many such people have subsequently had their sanction rescinded.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","216813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167573","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-05","<p /> <p>The Department doesn’t make an estimate the amount of benefit that would have been withheld as a result of benefit sanctions. Sanctions are designed to ensure claimants comply with their requirements in order to move off benefits and into work.</p><p> </p><p>The answer of 25 March 2013, Official Report, column 986W, on social security benefits made clear, it is not possible to robustly estimate the actual amounts withheld as we do not know what would have happened in the absence of sanctions. For example, of claimants who leave benefit during a sanction - some may have left irrespective of the sanction being applied, and some may have left because of the sanction.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-12-05T14:45:24.783Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167573/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167573/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167573/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-02","Jobseeker's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the Answer of 25 March 2013 to Question 149822 and pursuant to the Answer of 1 December 2014 to Question 215974, how much additional jobseeker's allowance in total claimants subject to a fixed sanction would have received if they had continued to be on the benefit for the length of time of their sanction in (a) 2012-13 and (b) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","216815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167574","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-05","<p /> <p>There are 3,713 people who have been referred to Atos Healthcare and, following a review by a healthcare professional, will require an appointment at the Assessment Centre in Bootle for a Work Capability Assessment (WCA).</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-12-05T10:09:20.003Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167574/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167574/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167574/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-02","Employment and Support Allowance: Bootle","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many employment and support allowance applicants are awaiting for a medical assessment at Bootle Assessment Centre.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","216747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167575","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-05","<p /> <p>For completed initial assessments for new claims to ESA for the period from October 2008 to December 2013 the median time taken from the issue of the ESA50 questionnaire to the claimant and the assessment date is 68 days.</p><p> </p><p>Medical assessments are not solely carried out by doctors but by a range of health care professionals.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-12-05T10:31:02.743Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167575/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167575/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167575/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-02","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average time has been that employment and support allowance applicants waited for a medical assessment by a doctor since the implementation of that allowance.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","216777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167576","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-05","<p /> <p>There is no contractual timeframe for carrying out medical assessments after receipt of an employment and support allowance application.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-12-05T10:35:20.4Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167576/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167576/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167576/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-02","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether there is a contractual timeframe for carrying out medical assessments after receipt of an employment and support allowance application.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","216784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167577","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-08","<p>The deadline for central government departments to confirm whether they wanted to participate in the ultra low emission vehicle readiness project was 13 October. No deadline was given to participants for the provision of data to the fleet review process. We currently expect the reviews to have concluded by 31 March 2015. We will give an update thereafter on how many vehicles will be integrated into each fleet.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","216904 ; 216905 ; 216906 ; 216908","2014-12-08T11:53:07.317Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167577/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167577/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167577/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-02","Official Cars","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 18 November 2014 to Question 214347, what deadline he has set for the Department for Work and Pensions' submission to the Government's fleet review.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","216907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167951","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-12-10","<p>Our co-operation with the Irish Government on security matters remains strong. Frances Fitzgerald, the Irish Justice and Equality Minister, has confirmed her commitment to continuing cross border co-operation to tackle the threat posed by terrorism. I also commend the outstanding work of the police on both sides of the border, whose recent successes in joint operations are testament to the strength of their working relationship.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-12-10T15:31:27.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167951/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167951/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167951/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-12-02","Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what assessment she has made of the adequacy of security co-operation between the UK and the Republic of Ireland.","false","Biography information for Adam Holloway","Gravesham","Mr Adam Holloway","906472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168438","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-08","<p /> <p>Youth unemployment has fallen nearly a quarter of a million over the last year – the second largest annual fall on record – down to 737,000.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-12-08T17:21:11Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168438/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/168438/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-02","Unemployment: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment he has made of levels of youth unemployment.","false","Biography information for Richard Graham","Gloucester","Richard Graham","906488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/169120","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-12-10","<p>Voluntary sector organisations provide invaluable support for those whose lives have been changed forever as a result of Northern Ireland’s troubled past.</p><p>I pay tribute to their work, which I know from my conversations with victims and their families is deeply appreciated by many in Northern Ireland and beyond.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2014-12-10T15:29:25.79Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/169120/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/169120/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/169120/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-12-02","Voluntary Organisations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what assessment her Department has made of the role played by the voluntary sector in dealing with the legacy of the past.","false","Biography information for David Mowat","Warrington South","David Mowat","906469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/169121","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-12-10","<p>I refer the hon Gentleman to the answer I gave earlier today to the hon Member for Glasgow North.</p><p> </p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2014-12-10T15:28:13.18Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/169121/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/169121/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/169121/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-12-02","Unemployment: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what steps she is taking to tackle youth unemployment in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","906468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166831","Home Office","false","2014-12-17","<p>Plans for a full and thorough consultation are currently being worked up. We recognise the importance of this measure and want to get it right. We will undertake a full consultation, involving key interested parties, including business and civil society.</p><p />",,"Lord Bates",,"2014-12-17T17:23:46.86Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166831/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166831/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166831/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-12-01","Slavery","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what arrangements they are making, and with whom, for consultation on the guidance to support businesses in their preparation of the slavery and trafficking statement to be required by the enactment of clause 51 of the Modern Slavery Bill; and whether those consultations will involve both business and civil society.","false","Biography information for Lord Judd",,"Lord Judd","HL3249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166832","Home Office","false","2014-12-17","<p>We are committed to consulting on this important issue and to getting it right. The timing of the consultation is under consideration and further details will be announced shortly.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2014-12-17T17:21:39.603Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166832/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166832/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166832/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-12-01","Slavery","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they intend to begin their consultations on the guidance to support businesses in their preparation of the slavery and trafficking statement to be required by the enactment of clause 51 of the Modern Slavery Bill before the House of Lords completes its scrutiny of the bill; and when they intend those consultations to be completed.","false","Biography information for Lord Judd",,"Lord Judd","HL3250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166833","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-12-08","<p>I can confirm that the debate held on 15 October (<em>Official Report</em>, column 267) regarding onshore wind farms has been brought to the attention of the Planning Inspectorate.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2014-12-08T12:14:36.757Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166833/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166833/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166833/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-12-01","Wind Power: Planning Permission","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the remarks by Baroness Verma on 15 October (HL Deb, col 267), whether the debate on onshore wind farms that day has been brought to the attention of the planning appeals inspectorate of the Department for Communities and Local Government.","false","Biography information for Lord Vinson",,"Lord Vinson","HL3251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166834","HM Treasury","false","2014-12-15","<p>Individuals’ personal allowance is shown as a tax free amount on their annual tax summary. The income tax calculation shows the taxable income above individuals’ personal allowance, payable at each tax rate.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Deighton",,"2014-12-15T17:35:00.143Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166834/answer","Biography information for Lord Deighton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166834/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166834/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-12-01","Taxation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government why the annual tax summaries sent to taxpayers show income tax as the amount which is 20 per cent of income and does not take account of allowances which reduce income tax to a lower figure.","false","Biography information for Lord Palmer of Childs Hill",,"Lord Palmer of Childs Hill","HL3252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166835","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-15","<p>We welcome the contribution made by UN Association-UK (UNA-UK) to the discussion on the UK’s role in the Human Rights Council.</p><p>The Government shares much of the analysis contained in the report. We have already achieved or are working towards delivering on a number of the recommendations. For example, we champion the independence of the Office of the UN High Commissioner for Human Rights; the majority of UK funding to the Office of the High Commissioner is not tied to specific conditions; and we engage with UN human rights mechanisms and support civil society engagement.</p><p>We share the ambitions stated in the report to strengthen the UN human rights mechanisms, lead by example and stimulate change on the ground; though we do not agree with the proposed methodology in every instance. For example, the recommendation to lengthen the mandates of country specific Special Rapporteurs to three years could in some cases undermine the efforts of countries to address their domestic human rights concerns quickly. We will continue to work closely with civil society, including UNA-UK, on our priorities for our second year on the Human Rights Council. The UK will be standing at the November 2016 Human Rights Council elections for the consecutive (2017-2019) term.</p><p>As I said during the launch of the UNA-UK foreign policy manifesto, as the Minister responsible for global human rights policy, I see my role as setting direction for the years to come through the promotion and protection of human rights bilaterally and in multilateral fora, including in the Human Rights Council.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2014-12-15T17:18:22.303Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166835/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166835/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166835/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-12-01","UN Human Rights Council","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their assessment of the report by the United Nations Association-UK <i>The UK's role on the UN Human Rights Council: Priorities for the UK's 2014–16 term</i>.","false","Biography information for Lord Avebury",,"Lord Avebury","HL3253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166836","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-10","The British Government has not recently discussed visa requirements for UK citizens visiting Kenya with the Kenyan government. British nationals require a visa to enter Kenya, which can be purchased on arrival. Within the EU, the European Commission only seeks coherence in visa requirements for Member States party to the Schengen Visa Code. The UK is not party to this code. Within the Commonwealth the UK is taking part in discussions which seek to facilitate the movement of Commonwealth citizens between member states.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2014-12-10T14:11:13.223Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166836/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166836/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166836/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-12-01","Kenya","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what conversations they have had with the government of Kenya about the requirement for United Kingdom citizens to have a visa to enter Kenya; and what steps they take within (1) the European Union, and (2) the Commonwealth, to encourage consistency in visa requirements for citizens of countries within those organisations.","false","Biography information for Lord Ashcroft",,"Lord Ashcroft","HL3254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166837","HM Treasury","false","2014-12-15","<p>The European Commission are responsible for calculating Member State contributions to the EU Budget using data provided by Eurostat, who collate and validate the data from Member States’ national statistical institutions, including for the UK the Office for National Statistics.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Prime Minister has been clear that it was completely unacceptable for the European Commission to demand a payment upfront on such a large scale and provide a month in which to pay it.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>European Finance Ministers met on the 7 November, and the Chancellor secured an agreement which meant the UK paid nothing on 1 December. Instead the payment will be made in instalments next year, and no fines or interest will be applied. The UK will also not pay £1.7 billion. The British rebate will apply in full, and apply simultaneously with the payment, not a year in arrears as normal. This means the Government has halved the bill, to around £850 million.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Lastly, the UK won agreement to change the regulations to ensure this never happens again. In the future, if any country receives an adjustment demand that is excessive, it will have the same opportunity to phase payments so that they are more affordable.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Deighton",,"2014-12-15T17:36:01.943Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166837/answer","Biography information for Lord Deighton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166837/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166837/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-12-01","EU Budget: Contributions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they are aware of the calculations used by the European Commission as a basis for the recent demand of £1.7 billion; and, if so, what is their assessment of those calculations.","false","Biography information for Lord Ashcroft",,"Lord Ashcroft","HL3255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166838","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-10","<p>The net additional cost of military operations in Libya in 2011 was £234 million.</p><p>Our military actions in Libya protected civilians under threat of attack and saved lives. All our actions were consistent with our obligations under international law and with United Nations Security Council Resolution 1973, which allowed all necessary measures to protect civilians and civilian populated areas under threat of attack.</p>",,"Lord Astor of Hever",,"2014-12-10T17:27:31.637Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166838/answer","Biography information for Lord Astor of Hever","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166838/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166838/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-01","Libya","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what was the cost to the United Kingdom of the military intervention in Libya; and what is their assessment of the benefits to the United Kingdom.","false","Biography information for Lord Ashcroft",,"Lord Ashcroft","HL3256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166839","Cabinet Office","false","2014-12-15","<p>In line with long-established convention, the Government does not comment on the proceedings of Cabinet or its committees.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Wallace of Saltaire",,"2014-12-15T17:07:23.53Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166839/answer","Biography information for Lord Wallace of Saltaire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166839/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166839/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-12-01","Sovereignty: Scotland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the decision to grant a referendum on independence to the Scottish people and the terms of that referendum were agreed by the Cabinet.","false","Biography information for Lord Ashcroft",,"Lord Ashcroft","HL3257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166840","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-15","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Astor of Hever",,"2014-12-15T17:23:52.953Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166840/answer","Biography information for Lord Astor of Hever","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166840/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166840/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-01","Military Decorations","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many gallantry medals have been awarded but not gazetted.","false","Biography information for Lord Ashcroft",,"Lord Ashcroft","HL3258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166841","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-15","<p>Construction of the St Helena Airport is more than 60% complete. It is currently within budget and on target to open for commercial flights in early 2016.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Northover",,"2014-12-15T15:44:58.793Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166841/answer","Biography information for Baroness Northover","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166841/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166841/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-01","St Helena","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what progress has been made in the construction of the St Helena airport; what is the estimated date that the first aircraft could land; and whether the construction is within budget.","false","Biography information for Lord Ashcroft",,"Lord Ashcroft","HL3259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166842","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-15","<p>The Global Summit to End Sexual Violence in Conflict had two primary objectives: to agree practical action to tackle impunity for the use of rape as a weapon of war, and to begin to shift global attitudes to these crimes. The Summit resulted in a number of practical outcomes and commitments, including the launch of the new International Protocol on the Documentation and Investigation of Sexual Violence in Conflict, various national action plans and strategies to address the issue, and the provision of additional support to survivors and organisations working with them. Our focus is now on implementing these outcomes.</p><p>The report from the Summit was published online on 10 December. It includes details of the commitments made at the Summit. We will continue to update Parliament on progress.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2014-12-15T16:40:09.66Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166842/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166842/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166842/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-12-01","Armed Conflict: Sexual Offences","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they will next publish a report on progress in implementing the commitments agreed and announced by United Kingdom Ministers at the Global Summit to End Sexual Violence in Conflict held in London in June.","false","Biography information for Lord McConnell of Glenscorrodale",,"Lord McConnell of Glenscorrodale","HL3260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166843","Department for International Development","false","2014-12-15","<p>The first annual progress report on commitments made at Girl Summit 2014 – including those announced by United Kingdom Ministers – will be issued in July 2015.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Northover",,"2014-12-15T14:10:20.857Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166843/answer","Biography information for Baroness Northover","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166843/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166843/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-12-01","Females: Equality","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they will next publish a report on progress in implementing the commitments agreed and announced by United Kingdom Ministers at the Girl Summit held in London in July.","false","Biography information for Lord McConnell of Glenscorrodale",,"Lord McConnell of Glenscorrodale","HL3261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166844","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-10","<p>There have been no discussions between UK Ministers and the Scottish government about the implementation of commitments agreed and announced by UK Ministers at the June Global Summit to End Sexual Violence in Conflict.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2014-12-10T14:11:45.093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166844/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166844/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166844/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-12-01","Armed Conflict: Sexual Offences","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the Scottish Government concerning implementing the commitments agreed and announced by United Kingdom Ministers at the Global Summit to End Sexual Violence in Conflict held in London in June.","false","Biography information for Lord McConnell of Glenscorrodale",,"Lord McConnell of Glenscorrodale","HL3262"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166845","Home Office","false","2014-12-17","<p>Scottish Ministers have been consulted on the implementation of the commitments agreed at the Girl Summit where they impact upon Scotland. This has included discussions on measures to strengthen law enforcement on female genital mutilation(FGM) with a particular focus on some of the legal barriers in cases of FGM.</p><p>As a result the Scottish Parliament's consent is being sought for the provisions on extra territorial jurisdiction in clause 67(2) of the Serious Crime Bill amending both the FGM Act 2003 and the Prohibition of Female Genital Mutilation (Scotland) Act 2005.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bates","HL3265","2014-12-17T17:43:41.863Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166845/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166845/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166845/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-12-01","Females: Equality","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the Scottish Government concerning implementing the commitments agreed and announced by United Kingdom Ministers at the Girl Summit held in London in July.","false","Biography information for Lord McConnell of Glenscorrodale",,"Lord McConnell of Glenscorrodale","HL3263"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166846","Home Office","false","2014-12-17","<p>The UK Government works closely with all devolved administrations to ensure the UK delivers a coordinated response to modern slavery. The Scottish Government is represented on the Inter-Departmental Ministerial Group on Modern Slavery, which leads this work. We have worked closely with the Scottish Government on the development of the Scottish Trafficking and Exploitation Bill, as well as the development of the Modern Slavery Bill, to ensure that legislation across the UK is coherent and effective.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2014-12-17T17:17:17.377Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166846/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166846/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-12-01","Exploitation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the Scottish Government concerning the relationship between the Modern Slavery Bill and the Human Trafficking and Exploitation Bill announced by the First Minister of Scotland on 26 November.","false","Biography information for Lord McConnell of Glenscorrodale",,"Lord McConnell of Glenscorrodale","HL3264"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166847","Home Office","false","2014-12-17","<p>Scottish Ministers have been consulted on the implementation of the commitments agreed at the Girl Summit where they impact upon Scotland. This has included discussions on measures to strengthen law enforcement on female genital mutilation(FGM) with a particular focus on some of the legal barriers in cases of FGM.</p><p>As a result the Scottish Parliament's consent is being sought for the provisions on extra territorial jurisdiction in clause 67(2) of the Serious Crime Bill amending both the FGM Act 2003 and the Prohibition of Female Genital Mutilation (Scotland) Act 2005.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bates","HL3263","2014-12-17T17:43:42.053Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166847/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166847/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166847/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-12-01","Female Genital Mutilation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the Scottish Government since the Girl Summit in July 2014 on the issue of prosecution for cases of female genital mutilation; and what specific actions have taken place as a result.","false","Biography information for Lord McConnell of Glenscorrodale",,"Lord McConnell of Glenscorrodale","HL3265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166848","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-09","<p>The level of profit bid by Inter City Railways Limited is commercially sensitive. It is not guaranteed and is commensurate with the risks associated with a franchise of this size and nature. The Government has put in place a profit cap and profit sharing mechanism to prevent any possibility of “over-compensation”.</p>",,"Baroness Kramer",,"2014-12-09T13:04:24.867Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166848/answer","Biography information for Baroness Kramer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166848/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166848/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-01","East Coast Railway Line","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their estimate of the annual profits to be made by the successful bidders for the East Coast rail franchise.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL3266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166849","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-10","<p>Inter City Railways Limited is a company registered in England and Wales and thus subject to relevant tax obligations. They are purchasing East Coast Main Line Limited as part of this franchise, which is also registered in England and Wales and compliant with relevant tax obligations. In addition, the Franchise Agreement includes provisions to monitor tax compliance during the life of the franchise.</p>",,"Baroness Kramer",,"2014-12-10T14:52:05.693Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166849/answer","Biography information for Baroness Kramer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166849/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166849/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-01","East Coast Railway Line","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what provision, if any, will be made in the contract for the East Coast rail franchise to ensure that all profits accruing to the franchisees are subject to United Kingdom taxes.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL3267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166850","Department of Health","false","2014-12-15","<p>There has been a managed move over the last decade from an over dependence on inpatient services towards a comprehensive, community-based service, including Crisis Resolution Teams and Home Treatment Teams.</p><p> </p><p>This means a shift in resources from inpatient care towards recovery-focused, community based services where the emphasis is on targeted, timely intervention to prevent crisis, or manage crises closer to home.</p><p> </p><p>However, the Government has made it clear that beds must always be available for those who need them.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government’s 2014-15 Mandate to NHS England states that every community must develop plans to ensure no-one in mental health crisis will be turned away.</p><p> </p><p>In February 2014 we published the mental health Crisis Care Concordat, which describes the roles and responsibilities of public services for improving outcomes for people experiencing a crisis.</p><p> </p><p>This makes it clear that local commissioners should commission a range of mental health services that allows beds to be available for a person in urgent need. Local areas are expected to commit to and agree to deliver their own ‘Mental Health Crisis Declaration’.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-12-15T12:27:23.973Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166850/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166850/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166850/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-12-01","Mental Health Services","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the availability of beds for mental health patients; and whether they have any plans to tackle any shortage.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL3268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166851","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-08","<p /> <p>In his speech on 28 November, the Prime Minister announced a number of proposals to restrict EU migrants’ access to welfare benefits. He made clear that the intention of his proposals was to make the immigration system fairer and reduce the current high level of migration from within the EU into the UK.</p>",,"Lord Freud",,"2014-12-08T12:14:09.78Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166851/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166851/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166851/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-12-01","Social Security Benefits: EU Nationals","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what effect they expect the Prime Minister’s proposals for curbs on welfare benefits for European Union migrants to have if implemented.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL3269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166852","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-15","<p>The Road Investment Strategy (RIS) committed a total of £15.2 billion in enhancement and long term maintenance of the network between 2015/16 and 2020/21 including 127 major enhancements, of which 84 were newly announced.</p><p> </p><p>This funding will be used to complete the road schemes on the Strategic Road Network currently under construction and begin construction of previously-announced schemes. It is anticipated that 69 of the 84 new road schemes announced as part of the RIS will enter construction over the course of the first Road Period which runs from 2015/16 to 2019/20.</p><p> </p><p>A further 15 schemes will be developed during this Road Period, but may not enter construction until the next Road Period. This is generally because the design of the scheme is complex and needs time to consider a number of potential options or because interaction between a proposed scheme and other committed work on the network means doing all of the work at once would cause significant disruption. This RIS commits funding to prepare this scheme so it can be ready to enter construction early in the next Road Period. Should the Strategic Highway Company be able to develop the scheme more quickly than expected, and if efficiency savings have freed surplus funds, construction may begin this Road Period.</p>",,"Baroness Kramer",,"2014-12-15T12:22:09.6Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166852/answer","Biography information for Baroness Kramer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166852/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166852/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-01","Roads: Construction","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the timeframe for their planned road improvement works announced by the Chancellor of the Exchequer on 1 December.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL3270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166853","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-15","<p>As part of the Government’s £15 billion investment in the strategic road network announced on the 1<sup>st</sup> December, the Department for Transport’s Road Investment Strategy includes committed funding for enhancements to the M6. This includes four schemes already committed to upgrade the most heavily congested parts of the M6 to Smart Motorway, which will add an extra lane through the use of the hard shoulder as part of the &quot;smart spine&quot;, a 145 mile corridor linking London and Manchester and improvements to three junctions to increase capacity and provide better access to local employment and development sites.</p>",,"Baroness Kramer",,"2014-12-15T12:22:54.6Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166853/answer","Biography information for Baroness Kramer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166853/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166853/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-12-01","M6","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to invest in improving the M6.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL3271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166854","Department of Health","false","2014-12-15","<p>The UK National Screening Committee (UK NSC) advises Ministers and the National Health Service in all four countries about all aspects of screening policy and supports implementation. It keeps evidence in support of new programmes under review. Where stakeholder organisations or individuals feel that there is enough evidence published in peer reviewed journals to consider screening for a condition they can submit a proposal to the UK NSC. For further information please see the UK NSC’s website:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.screening.nhs.uk/policyreview__" target="_blank">http://www.screening.nhs.uk/policyreview</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In 2011, the UK NSC recommended that screening for bowel cancer using flexible sigmoidoscopy should be piloted as part of the NHS Bowel Cancer Screening Programme. NHS England and Public Health England are working together to set up screening centres for Bowel Scope Screening (BSS), with over 30% operational by the end of March 2014. Our commitment is to have BSS rolled out to 60% of screening centres in England by the end of March 2015, and to all screening centres in England by the end of 2016.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In early 2015 the UK Collaborative Trial of Ovarian Cancer Screening is due to be published and the NELSON study, a randomised controlled lung cancer screening trial using multi-slice low-dose CT in high risk men and women, is expected to end in December 2015. Following publication of the results of these two studies the UK NSC will review its recommendation on screening women for ovarian cancer and screening current and former smokers for lung cancer.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-12-15T12:26:07.533Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166854/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166854/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166854/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-12-01","Cancer","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have any plans to increase screening for cancers.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL3272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166855","Department of Health","false","2014-12-15","<p>Dementia is a key priority for this Government and we are committed to ensuring people with dementia and their carers receive the best possible care in all care settings. That is why in 2012 we launched the first ever Prime Minister’s Challenge on dementia to increase diagnosis rates, raise awareness and understanding and double funding for research in dementia by 2015.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>A number of steps have been taken to help care for dementia patients:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>- on 1 April 2014 we have put in place a new Dementia Directed Enhanced Service, which has had over 80% take up by general practitioners (GPs) to reward practices for facilitating timely diagnosis and support for people with dementia. An additional enhanced service for GPs will run between October 2014 and March 2015 with a view to a further boost to diagnosis;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>- in the hospital setting, through the Dementia Commissioning for Quality and Innovation (CQUIN) reward (introduced from April 2012), with around 4,000 referrals a month, it is clear that more people with dementia in hospitals are being identified and assessed. Between April 2013 and June 2014 there have been 59,961 referrals as a result of the introduction of this CQUIN goal;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>- the Dementia Care &amp; Support Compact, the care sector’s own response to the Prime Minister’s Challenge on Dementia, sets out a commitment to support the delivery of the challenge and improve care and support for people with dementia, their carers and families;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>- Health Education England (HEE), Skills for Care and Skills for Health launched the pilot for the new Care Certificate on 28 April 2014. Taking place across a range of health and social care settings, the pilots are testing a set of standards designed to help employers to assess not only workers’ skills, but also the knowledge, behaviours and values that are required to deliver compassionate and quality care. The pilots are nearing completion. Subject to evaluation, we plan to introduce the Care Certificate by 1 April 2015;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>- the Government’s refreshed Mandate to HEE, published on 1 May 2014, builds on the existing ambition to have 100,000 National Health Service staff receive Tier 1 training on dementia by setting an ambition for a further 250,000 NHS staff to receive Tier 1 training on dementia by March 2015, with the tools and training opportunities being made available to all staff by the end of 2018;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>- 72 communities across England have signed up to the national Dementia Friendly Communities recognition process, with an increased ambition to reach 75 by March 2015;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>- on 7 May 2014, Public Health England and the Alzheimer’s Society launched a major new campaign with the aim of securing one million people to become dementia friends by March 2015. The campaign is aimed at improving understanding and attitudes about dementia and towards people with the condition. There are currently over 579,000 Dementia Friends; and</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>- we have made available £50 million capital funding for 2013-14 for the NHS and local authorities to work with providers to create better care environments to help people with dementia live well with the condition. The projects are now in the process of being evaluated and we will disseminate the key recommendations by the end of the year.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2014-12-15T14:16:30.573Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166855/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166855/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166855/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-12-01","Dementia","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to ensure adequate care for dementia sufferers.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL3273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166856","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-15","<p>Captain Bairnsfather’s cartoons played a significant role in maintaining the morale of British troops during the First World War. It is therefore right that his contribution to the war effort is recognised. He is commemorated by the English Heritage Blue Plaque at 1 Sterling Street in Knightsbridge, London. The plaque was erected in 1981 to commemorate the site of one of his old studios. He is also commemorated by plaques at his former home in Stratford-upon-Avon and the Royal British Legion Club in Colwall, near Malvern in Worcestershire. The Ministry of Defence has no further plans to commemorate Captain Bairnsfather’s contribution.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Astor of Hever",,"2014-12-15T17:31:26.837Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166856/answer","Biography information for Lord Astor of Hever","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166856/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166856/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-12-01","World War I","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to grant official recognition to Captain Bruce Bairnsfather for the contribution of his cartoons to the morale of the men on the fighting front, the nation on the home front, and United Kingdom allies in the 1914–18 war.","false","Biography information for Lord Faulkner of Worcester",,"Lord Faulkner of Worcester","HL3274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166857","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-12-04","<p>Draft regulations have been drawn up and have been submitted to the European Commission for comment under the terms of the Technical Standards Directive. ​These regulations will end unsupervised stakes above £50 by requiring customers to interact with betting shop staff or open an account before being permitted to proceed. We intend for these to come into force on the April 2015 common commencement date.</p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2014-12-04T14:51:43.117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166857/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166857/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166857/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-12-01","Gaming Machines","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to introduce further regulations on B2 gaming machines.","false","Biography information for Lord Clement-Jones",,"Lord Clement-Jones","HL3275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166858","HM Treasury","false","2014-12-15","<p>The Government has decided to proceed with a single set of rules to apply to all clubs following detailed consultation across the sector. A single set of rules setting out clear tests will make it simpler and easier for clubs to understand and comply with their responsibilities. The rules are as simple as possible, bearing in mind they apply to almost one hundred different sports, operating in often very different ways.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>However, the Government does recognise that the existing administrative arrangements that apply when an existing CASC changes its status – such as when an unincorporated association changes into a company – can be burdensome. HMRC will therefore introduce a simpler, more streamlined process within the existing legislative framework.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Deighton",,"2014-12-15T17:23:03.297Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166858/answer","Biography information for Lord Deighton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166858/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166858/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-12-01","Community Amateur Sports Clubs Scheme","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Statement by Lord Deighton on 25 November 2013 (WS 76–8), whether they consider that the new draft regulations on registration and eligibility for community amateur sports clubs meet Lord Deighton's pledge to "keep the rules as simple as possible".","false","Biography information for Lord Clement-Jones",,"Lord Clement-Jones","HL3276"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166859","Department of Health","false","2014-12-15","<p>The NHS Health Check is offered to all 40-74 year olds without existing disease once every five years. The check assesses family history of cardiovascular disease, smoking status, alcohol use, levels of physical activity, body mass index, cholesterol and blood pressure and uses information on age, gender and ethnicity to identify an individual’s 10-year risk of developing cardiovascular disease. Where the results of these tests indicate that a person is at high risk of diabetes and chronic kidney disease then additional diagnostic tests, specifically HbA1c or serum creatinine respectively, are undertaken.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Data on eligible population having an NHS Health Check has been collected nationally since 2011-12. Of those eligible 7.1%, 8.0% and 9.0% had an NHS Health Check in 2011-12, 2012-13 and 2013-14 respectively.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Cost-benefit modelling estimates the cost of the programme to be £332 million each year at full roll out, with the average annual benefit to be £3.678 billion. The cost-benefits of the programme primarily arise from the opportunity it presents to prevent 1,600 heart attacks and strokes, and save at least 650 lives each year. It also offers the opportunity to prevent over 4,000 people a year from developing diabetes and detect at least 20,000 cases of diabetes or kidney disease earlier, allowing individuals’ health to be better managed and improve their quality of life.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The findings from this cost-benefit modelling further suggest that the programme is cost-effective, with potential savings to the National Health Service of around £57 million per year after four years, rising to £176 million per year after 15 years. This equates to a cost per quality-adjusted life-year of around £3,000, which is considerably lower than the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence’s threshold.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is committed to bringing ever-greater scientific and clinical rigour to the programme. Public Health England has established an Expert Scientific Clinical and Advisory panel, formed of eminent clinicians and academics, which keep the evidence under review and have recently published research priorities for consultation.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Cochrane Centre review does add to the existing evidence base, however, its generalisability to the NHS Health Check is limited. The studies that the review considers are old, predominantly published in the 1960s. They were also undertaken on people from different age groups and the ‘health checks’ that they consider are not directly comparable to the NHS Health Check. For example, the age of the studies means that the majority were carried out before statins were introduced into primary care.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe","HL3278 ; HL3279 ; HL3280 ; HL3281 ; HL3282","2014-12-15T12:19:08.68Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166859/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166859/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166859/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-12-01","Health: Screening","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what percentage of the eligible population have had an appointment under the NHS Health Check Scheme in each year since the scheme began.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL3277"
