"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167040","Department of Health","false","2014-12-10","<p>The contract of employment for the Chief Executive of NHS England is held between NHS England and the Chief Executive. The Department of Health does not comment on the terms of individual contracts held between NHS England and its employees.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-12-10T16:54:35.347Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167040/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167040/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167040/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-12-01","NHS: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether the chief executive of NHS England is permitted under his contract to publicly welcome financial commitments to the NHS made by the Shadow Secretary of State for Health.","false","Biography information for Frank Dobson","Holborn and St Pancras","Frank Dobson","216669"
